%N A393427 Decimal expansion of the probability that the centroid of a given triangle lies within the triangle formed by three points chosen uniformly and independently at random from the interior of that given triangle.
%C A393427 The probability does not depend on the shape of the given triangle.
%C A393427 The probability was apparently first published by the Hungarian mathematician András Prékopa (1929-2016) in 1972. It was presented by him at the 5th International Symposium on Mathematical Programming (London, 1964).
%C A393427 The corresponding probability when the three points are chosen inside a square or a disk is 1/4 in each case.
%H A393427 Sylvia Halász and David J. Kleitman, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1002/sapm1974533225">A note on random triangles</a>, Studies in Applied Mathematics, Vol. 53, No. 3 (1974), pp. 225-237.
%H A393427 Eugen J. Ionaşcu, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s12215-018-0364-8">Random triangles in planar regions</a>, Rendiconti del Circolo Matematico di Palermo, Series 2, Vol. 68 (2019), pp. 363-383; <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1612.08619">arXiv preprint</a>, arXiv:1612.08619 [math.HO], 2016-2018.
%H A393427 A. Prékopa, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02018666">On the number of vertices of random convex polyhedra</a>, Periodiea Mathematica Hungarica, Vol. 2, No. 1-4 (1972), pp. 259-282; <a href="https://rutcor.rutgers.edu/~prekopa/number.pdf">author's copy</a>.
%F A393427 Equals 2/27 + 20*log(2)/81 (Prékopa, 1972, p. 279, eq. (5.24)).
